The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, March 27, 2004 				Metro Recommends
				 																The TV Show				 																																	Discovery, Sunday, 7 pm One of the greatest leaders of all time, Alexander the Greats death at the age of 32 remains a mystery to this day. The programme provides fresh insights into the life and death of the Greek hero, reliving the mastery and madness of the man who is said to have achieved the impossible The chat				 																																	(Srijan, Saturday, 5.30 pm) A poetry adda will take the audience on a journey through the world of the poetry of Sankha Ghosh (picture above), in an interactive session. This will be followed by a 20-minute reading of a playlet, Usha, by Ashoke Vishwanathan The Book				 																																	(Ashok Roy) The book profiles 21 living legends of Indian classical music, from Ustad Amjad Ali Khan to Pandit Bhimsen Joshi. Through a brief but captivating biography of each musician, a collage of photographs and interviews, the book attempts to portray Indian classical music itself The album				 																																	(George Michael) The singers back with Patience  supposedly his last commercial release. Its refreshingly light and frank (like Amazing, the first single of the album) by Michaels standards. Hauntingly personal ballads and up-tempo summer anthems fit just as snugly. The 14-track Patience is worth the eight-year wait 

